# Visual COBOL Documentation Sources

## RAG MCP Server

The primary source for Visual COBOL documentation is the **visual-cobol-docs** RAG MCP server:

```
MCP Server: user-visual-cobol-docs
Tool: query_docs
Status: Available and indexed
```

### How to query

```json
{
  "server": "user-visual-cobol-docs",
  "toolName": "query_docs",
  "arguments": { "query": "your question here", "n_results": 5 }
}
```

### What it contains

The RAG index is built from three documentation sets in `C:\opt\src\AiDoc\library\visual-cobol-docs\`:

| Source Folder | Content |
|---|---|
| `Rocket-Visual-Cobol-Messages-Reference-Vesion-11` | Compiler messages (COBCH series), runtime messages (MFCWD series), DB2 preprocessor messages (COBDB series) |
| `Rocket-Visual-Cobol-Documentation-Version-11` | Full product documentation: compiler directives, command-line reference, installation, build tools, IDE integration |
| `Rocket-Visual-Cobol-For-VisualStudio-2022-Version-11` | VS 2022 specific integration, project properties, debugging, deployment |

### Example queries that return good results

- `"compiler directives sourceformat anim cobidy"` — directive reference
- `"COBCH0779 compiler message"` — specific error code lookup
- `"cobol.exe command line compiler usage"` — CLI compilation guide
- `"DB2 SQL preprocessor directives"` — DB2 integration
- `"Rocket Visual COBOL installation path Windows"` — install paths
- `"mfcrown directives.mf utility"` — new v11 tooling

