## Key Technical Facts (from RAG + docs)

### Product naming

- **Vendor:** Rocket Software (formerly Micro Focus)
- **Product:** Rocket Visual COBOL 11.0
- **Installer:** `vcvs2022_110.exe` (VS 2022 integration), `vcbt_110.exe` (Build Tools)

### Install paths

| Path | Description |
|---|---|
| `C:\Program Files (x86)\Rocket Software\Visual COBOL\` | Current Rocket Software install (v11) |
| `C:\Program Files (x86)\Micro Focus\Visual COBOL\` | Legacy Micro Focus install (pre-Rocket acquisition) |
| `C:\Program Files (x86)\Micro Focus\Net Express 5.1\` | Legacy Net Express (predecessor product) |

Scripts must auto-detect which path exists. Rocket path takes priority.

### Compiler directives (v11 changes from RAG)

Key directives renamed in v11 (old names still accepted but listings show new names):
- `MFCOMMENT` → `ALTCOMMENT`
- `MFLEVEL` / `MF` → `LANGLEVEL`
- `MFSYNC` → `SYNC`
- `DIALECT"MF"` → `DIALECT"ROCKET"`
- `SIGN"MF"` → `SIGN"ROCKET"`
- `COPYSEARCH"MF"` → `COPYSEARCH"ROCKET"`

New in v11:
- `COPYDIR` — single directory for copybook search (accumulative, searched before COPYPATH)
- `LEVEL78-PREC` — BODMAS precedence for level-78 VALUE clause evaluation
- `mfcrown` — new CLI utility for editing `directives.mf` files, includes lint and auto-determine

### VCPATH folder structure

```
%VCPATH%\
├── bnd\          Bind files (.bnd)
├── cfg\          Compiler directives (.dir) and run scripts
├── dir\          Per-file compiler directive files (generated)
├── int\          Compiled intermediate files (.int)
├── lst\          Listing files (.lst)
├── log\          Compilation logs
├── net\          Mapped network paths (srv\, drv\)
├── tmp\          Temporary files
└── src\
    ├── bat\      Batch files
    ├── rex\      REXX scripts
    ├── psh\      PowerShell scripts
    └── cbl\      COBOL sources
        ├── cpy\  Copybooks (.cpy, .cpx, .cpb, .dcl)
        │   └── sys\cpy\  System copybooks
        └── imp\  Import files
```

### Environment variables

| Variable | Purpose | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `VCPATH` | Root of the COBOL workspace | `C:\fkavd\Dedge2` |
| `COBCPY` | Copybook search path | `%VCPATH%\src\cbl\cpy;%VCPATH%\src\cbl\cpy\sys\cpy;%VCPATH%\src\cbl` |
| `COBPATH` | INT file search path | `%VCPATH%\int;%VCPATH%\gs;%VCPATH%\src\cbl` |
| `COBDIR` | Compiler base directory | `C:\Program Files (x86)\Rocket Software\Visual COBOL` |
| `COBMODE` | Compilation bit mode | `32` or `64` |
| `MFVSSW` | Compiler switches | `/c /f` |

### DB2 integration

The SQL compiler directive file (`VcCompilerDirectivesSql.dir`) controls DB2 preprocessing:
- `DB2(DB=DB2DEV)` — target database alias
- `DB2(COLLECTION=DBM)` — bind package collection
- `DB2(UDB-VERSION=V9)` — DB2 UDB version target
- `DB2(BIND)` — auto-bind after compile
- `DB2(BINDDIR=%VCPATH%\bnd)` — bind output directory

## INT File Recompilation: Disqualifier Checklist

**Verdict: All .INT files from Net Express 5.1 MUST be recompiled for Visual COBOL 11.**

See `AnalysisResult-IntFileRecompilation.md` for the full analysis. Summary of disqualifiers below.

### Hard Blockers (crash or refuse to load)

| ID | Disqualifier | Error |
|---|---|---|
| A1 | .GNT files from Net Express are explicitly blocked | Files ignored |
| A2 | 32-bit INT on 64-bit runtime (COBMODE defaults to 64 since R4+) | `COBRT211` |
| A3 | Linked executables/shared objects from older COBOL systems incompatible | `COBRT211` |
| A4 | OO programs compiled with incompatible compiler version | `COBRT212` |
| A5 | `coblongjmp()` in error/exit/signal handlers now enforced as fatal | `COBRT131` |
| A6 | COMMUNICATION SECTION removed from runtime support | `COBCH1895` / undefined |
| A7 | Class Library version mismatch (Net Express vs Visual COBOL) | `COBRT111` |
| A8 | IDY symbol files from Net Express incompatible | `COBOP070` |

### Silent Data Corruption (runs but wrong results)

| ID | Disqualifier | Impact |
|---|---|---|
| B1 | FCD format default changed FCD2 → FCD3 | File I/O wrong results / `RTS114` |
| B2 | IDXFORMAT default changed 4 → 8 | Indexed files unreadable cross-format |
| B3 | FILEMAXSIZE default changed 4 → 8 | Large file handling differs |
| B4 | DBCS literal treatment changed (NCHAR padding) | String comparisons wrong |
| B5 | Fixed Binary (p<=7) default changed to 8-bit signed | Arithmetic results differ |
| B6 | FCD must be initialized with binary zeros in unused areas | `RTS114` / unpredictable |
| B7 | MFALLOC_PCFILE default changed N → Y | Unexpected file creation |

### Environment / Configuration Conflicts

| ID | Disqualifier | Impact |
|---|---|---|
| C1 | COBMODE default 32-bit → 64-bit | Wrong execution mode |
| C2 | COBREG_PARSED conflict when both products installed | Tool interference |
| C3 | DB2 ECM updated for 64-bit mode | Must recompile + rebind |
| C4 | Licensing: SafeNet Sentinel removed, RocketPass required | Runtime refuses to execute |
| C5 | ILUSING scope changed (file-only, not global) | Type resolution fails |
| C6 | Report Writer HOSTRW behavior changed | Report output differs |

### Removed Features

| ID | Feature | Status |
|---|---|---|
| D1 | Animator debugger | Removed |
| D2 | Data Tools (converter, editor, fix index, IMS) | Removed |
| D3 | FaultFinder diagnostic | Removed |
| D4 | Dialog System | Compatibility AddPack only, threading changed |
| D5 | command_line_linkage tunable | Deprecated |

### Quick Source Scan Patterns

When checking `.CBL` source for disqualifiers before deciding to recompile:

```
COMMUNICATION SECTION    → A6
coblongjmp               → A5
EXTFH / EXTSM            → B1, B6
NCHAR / DBCS             → B4
EXEC SQL                 → C3
FAULTFIND                → D3
ILUSING                  → C5
```

## Script Standards for This Folder

All scripts in this folder follow these conventions:
- `#Requires -Version 7.0` and `[CmdletBinding()]`
- `Import-Module GlobalFunctions -Force` for logging (`Write-LogMessage`) and SMS (`Send-Sms`)
- Auto-detect compiler path: Rocket Software first, Micro Focus fallback
- `$env:VCPATH` with default `C:\fkavd\Dedge2`
- No external encoding tools — use .NET `[System.Text.Encoding]::GetEncoding(1252)` for ANSI files
